130
00:04:28,050 --> 00:04:30,390
Not all self-healing
polymers are the same,

131
00:04:30,390 --> 00:04:31,590
and it seems that there are,

132
00:04:31,590 --> 00:04:33,780
at least, two possible explanations

133
00:04:33,780 --> 00:04:36,120
for what's happening with this one.

134
00:04:36,120 --> 00:04:38,940
The first is a polymerization reaction,

135
00:04:38,940 --> 00:04:41,910
and the second is a crosslinking reaction.

136
00:04:41,910 --> 00:04:44,130
A polymerization reaction
is just a reaction

137
00:04:44,130 --> 00:04:46,830
that joins lots of small
molecules together,

138
00:04:46,830 --> 00:04:49,020
into long chain molecules,

139
00:04:49,020 --> 00:04:50,250
into polymers.

140
00:04:50,250 --> 00:04:52,830
It can also be when you take
two existing polymer chains

141
00:04:52,830 --> 00:04:56,250
and join them together into
one longer polymer chain,

142
00:04:56,250 --> 00:04:57,990
and that's potentially what's happening

143
00:04:57,990 --> 00:04:59,610
with this self-healing polymer.

144
00:04:59,610 --> 00:05:02,550
When you bring two surfaces together,

145
00:05:02,550 --> 00:05:05,790
some of the ends of the
polymers on one surface

146
00:05:05,790 --> 00:05:08,430
are joining to some of
the ends of the polymers

147
00:05:08,430 --> 00:05:10,260
on the other surface,

148
00:05:10,260 --> 00:05:12,630
creating longer polymer chains

149
00:05:12,630 --> 00:05:15,180
that span the break.

150
00:05:15,180 --> 00:05:16,410
Unlike with the plastic,

151
00:05:16,410 --> 00:05:18,660
this polymerization reaction can happen

152
00:05:18,660 --> 00:05:19,770
at room temperature,

153
00:05:19,770 --> 00:05:22,020
perhaps because when
you break the polymers,

154
00:05:22,020 --> 00:05:25,230
you're not left with
highly reactive radicals,

155
00:05:25,230 --> 00:05:28,950
or perhaps because of the
presence of a catalyst.

156
00:05:28,950 --> 00:05:30,330
Actually, that might explain

157
00:05:30,330 --> 00:05:32,640
why the polymer isn't sticky.

158
00:05:32,640 --> 00:05:35,730
If the catalyst has a high specificity

159
00:05:35,730 --> 00:05:38,940
to that particular
polymerization reaction,

160
00:05:38,940 --> 00:05:41,130
and very few others,

161
00:05:41,130 --> 00:05:45,480
that would explain why
it's only sticky to itself.

162
00:05:45,480 --> 00:05:46,590
The second possibility,

163
00:05:46,590 --> 00:05:47,910
crosslinking, is what happens

164
00:05:47,910 --> 00:05:50,460
when you have lots of individual chains,

165
00:05:50,460 --> 00:05:52,560
and you link them together

166
00:05:52,560 --> 00:05:55,470
at different positions along the chain.

167
00:05:55,470 --> 00:05:58,710
Like, for example, I've got
loads of little chains here,

168
00:05:58,710 --> 00:06:01,380
and maybe I'm gonna join
these two chains together

169
00:06:01,380 --> 00:06:02,310
at this point,

170
00:06:02,310 --> 00:06:03,750
these two chains together at this point,

171
00:06:03,750 --> 00:06:04,740
and so on.

172
00:06:04,740 --> 00:06:07,110
Crosslinking strengthens a polymer.

173
00:06:07,110 --> 00:06:10,740
For example, I've got
this liquid latex here,

174
00:06:10,740 --> 00:06:13,230
it's liquid, because the
individual polymer chains

175
00:06:13,230 --> 00:06:15,840
are able to slide over each other,

176
00:06:15,840 --> 00:06:17,640
but I can cause crosslinks to form

177
00:06:17,640 --> 00:06:19,560
between these separate chains

178
00:06:19,560 --> 00:06:21,240
by changing the pH.

179
00:06:21,240 --> 00:06:23,040
So, by adding vinegar,

180
00:06:23,040 --> 00:06:25,830
for example, I turn this liquid latex

181
00:06:25,830 --> 00:06:28,170
into a bouncy ball.

182
00:06:28,170 --> 00:06:30,900
It's interesting to think that before,

183
00:06:30,900 --> 00:06:33,090
I had lots of individual molecules,

184
00:06:33,090 --> 00:06:36,150
and now, I have one giant molecule,

185
00:06:36,150 --> 00:06:37,890
the size of a bouncy ball.

186
00:06:37,890 --> 00:06:41,220
And this is true for
things like car tires.

187
00:06:41,220 --> 00:06:44,550
This car tire is one giant molecule.

188
00:06:44,550 --> 00:06:46,710
How does this relate to
self-healing polymers?

189
00:06:46,710 --> 00:06:48,810
Well, when two surfaces of the polymer

190
00:06:48,810 --> 00:06:49,920
are brought together,

191
00:06:49,920 --> 00:06:51,420
chains on one surface,

192
00:06:51,420 --> 00:06:53,220
and chains on the other surface,

193
00:06:53,220 --> 00:06:54,540
come into contact,

194
00:06:54,540 --> 00:06:57,030
and a crosslinking reaction occurs.

195
00:06:57,030 --> 00:06:58,920
It's interesting that
that reaction can happen

196
00:06:58,920 --> 00:07:00,000
at room temperature.

197
00:07:00,000 --> 00:07:01,410
And it's interesting that the polymer

198
00:07:01,410 --> 00:07:03,810
is able to create bonds with itself,

199
00:07:03,810 --> 00:07:05,910
but not other things.

200
00:07:05,910 --> 00:07:08,040
It's interesting that it's not sticky.

201
00:07:08,040 --> 00:07:09,420
Whether it's a crosslinking reaction

202
00:07:09,420 --> 00:07:10,920
or a polymerization reaction,

203
00:07:10,920 --> 00:07:13,320
the explanation for why this substance

204
00:07:13,320 --> 00:07:14,760
is only sticky to itself,

205
00:07:14,760 --> 00:07:15,840
and not other things,

206
00:07:15,840 --> 00:07:18,630
seems to be in the molecular detail,

207
00:07:18,630 --> 00:07:21,540
